{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The scoring model assigns the correct risk score when a transaction exceeds the configured amount threshold for its merchant category.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Failure boundary is rule logic (amount vs category threshold -> score), which is local computation with config input. Behavior text does not require real DB/network/subprocess or real AI/ML judgment. Higher levels were considered and rejected because the behavior is explicitly about one scoring-rule outcome, not cross-module handoff.","test_description":"Call the scoring function with table-driven fixtures: merchant category thresholds, transaction amounts around boundary (below/equal/above), and expected numeric score deltas. Include edge cases for exact-threshold and category-specific overrides.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.83,"Integration":0.14,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The risk model identifies a fraudulent transaction pattern (e.g., rapid small purchases from different geographies) even when no single rule threshold is exceeded.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on the model’s fraud judgment from contextual pattern signals, i.e., real AI/ML output content. A stubbed model would hide true misclassification failures and always pass if hardcoded. Workflow is rejected because this behavior is one model decision, not multiple agentic decisions in sequence.","test_description":"Run the real risk model on a labeled evaluation slice containing cross-geo rapid-small-purchase fraud patterns where rule thresholds are individually not breached. Assert fraud probability/label clears agreed detection criteria (e.g., threshold or recall on this slice).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.84,"Workflow":0.04}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The velocity check in the scoring model correctly counts the number of transactions within the configured time window per user.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"The described failure is counting/window logic per user, which can be reproduced with in-memory transaction timestamps and user IDs. Behavior text does not require real OS/network/subprocess. Integration was considered but rejected because no concrete storage or inter-module boundary is specified in the behavior.","test_description":"Test velocity-count function with synthetic per-user transaction streams and a fixed clock: include boundary timestamps at window start/end, mixed users, out-of-window events, and unordered inputs. Assert exact count used for scoring.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.72,"Integration":0.24,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A transaction flagged by the risk model but not by the scoring model is still held for review — the models operate as an OR gate, not AND.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is a module-handoff/orchestration behavior: combine outputs from two model components into hold/review decision. Unit-only testing of a boolean helper can miss wiring/DTO mapping bugs at service boundaries. Higher levels rejected: no real OS/network/subprocess requirement; no dependence on real model output quality because fixed model outputs are sufficient for OR semantics.","test_description":"Wire fraud-decision service with stubbed scoring and risk model adapters returning controlled outputs. Verify hold=true for (risk=true, scoring=false), and add companion cases for other boolean combinations to enforce OR semantics end-to-end across service modules.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.21,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The combined output includes both the numeric risk score and the risk model's fraud probability, so the reviewer can see which model flagged the transaction and why.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is output composition/contract across modules (scoring output + risk output -> reviewer payload). Unit tests of a mapper alone can miss missing-field/serialization contract issues when components are wired. Agentic rejected because this behavior checks presence/propagation of fields, not quality of model judgment.","test_description":"Exercise the assembled decision endpoint/service with controlled model outputs; assert response schema contains numeric risk score, fraud probability, and model-specific flag metadata used by reviewer UI. Validate types and field names expected by downstream consumer.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
